The paper deals with temporal action localization in videos, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new method for modeling temporal relationships between candidate proposals, which involves learning discriminative features. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses a sampling strategy to address the unbalanced context problem, which is a common issue in information retrieval. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
